Class Set

    • Math.Set.Set

    public class Set

        public Set(EquationSystem pEqSys)

        Parameters:
        pEqSys - The EquationSystem that the Set will be based off of.

      • Set

        public Set(EquationSystem pEqSys,
           double min,
           double max,
           double cStep)
        Creates a Set based off the EquationSystem eq.
        The arr1 of the Set is defined by the code: int pos = 0; for(double i = min; i < max; i += (max - min) / cStep, pos++) arr1[pos] = i;
        The arr2 of the Set is defined by the code: int pos = 0; for(double i = min; i < max; i += (max - min) / cStep, pos++) arr2[pos] = pred(i, pEqSys);
        Parameters:
        pEqSys - The EquationSystem that the Set will be based off of.
        min - The starting value for arr1.
        max - The ending value for arr1.
        cStep - The step size for arr1.
        See Also:
        pred(double,EquationSystem)
